-- Mori Building to Sell Portion of Shanghai Financial Tower, Nikkei Reports
-- B y   N a o k o   F u j i m u r a
-- 2010-11-03T00:00:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/mori-building-to-sell-portion-of-shanghai-s-tallest-tower-nikkei-reports.html
 Mori Building Co. plans to sell part
of its Shanghai World Financial Center for between 40 billion
yen ($496 million) and 50 billion yen to recoup development
costs, the Nikkei newspaper reported, without saying where it
got the information. The Tokyo-based company has started
reviewing potential buyers through a local real estate broker,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
